# ======================Access RDS using vpc peering (same-region)===================

1. Create VPC-1 (EC2 VPC)
Go to: VPC → Create VPC
Settings:
Name: VPC-EC2
IPv4 CIDR: 10.0.0.0/16
Tenancy: Default
Click Create

2. Create Subnet for EC2
Go to: Subnets → Create Subnet
VPC: VPC-EC2
Name: EC2-Subnet
AZ: ap-south-1a
CIDR: 10.0.1.0/24
Create.

3. Create Internet Gateway (for EC2 SSH)
Go to: Internet Gateways → Create
Name: EC2-IGW
Attach to: VPC-EC2

4. Create Route Table for EC2 
Go to: Route Tables → Create
Name: EC2-RT
VPC: VPC-EC2
Edit Routes:
Add:
Destination	- 0.0.0.0/0 
Target - 	Internet Gateway
Associate this route table with EC2-Subnet.

5. Create EC2 Security Group
Go to: EC2 → Security Groups → Create
Name: EC2-SG
VPC: VPC-EC2
Inbound:
SSH (22) → Your IP
MySQL (3306) → Allow All (for now testing)

6. Launch EC2 Instance
Go to: EC2 → Launch Instance
AMI: Ubuntu
Instance type: t2.micro
VPC: VPC-EC2
Subnet: EC2-Subnet
Auto assign Public IP: Enable
Security Group: EC2-SG
Key Pair: Select/Create

7. Create VPC-2 (RDS VPC)
Go to: VPC → Create VPC
Name: VPC-RDS
CIDR: 10.1.0.0/16
Create.

8. Create Private Subnets for RDS
Create 2 subnets (RDS needs 2 AZs):

Subnet 1:
Name: RDS-Subnet-1
CIDR: 10.1.1.0/24
AZ: ap-south-1a

Subnet 2:
Name: RDS-Subnet-2
CIDR: 10.1.2.0/24
AZ: ap-south-1b

9. Create RDS Subnet Group
Go to: RDS → Subnet Groups → Create
Name: rds-subnet-group
VPC: VPC-RDS
Add both subnets
Create.

10. Create RDS Security Group
Go to: EC2 → Security Groups → Create
Name: RDS-SG
VPC: VPC-RDS
Inbound:
MySQL (3306)
Source: 10.0.0.0/16 (EC2 VPC CIDR)
Outbound:
Allow All

11. Create RDS Database
Go to: RDS → Create Database
Engine: MySQL
Template: Free tier
DB identifier: mydb
Username: admin
Password: choose

Network:
VPC: VPC-RDS
Subnet group: rds-subnet-group
Public Access: No
Security Group: RDS-SG
Create DB.
Wait until status: Available

12. Create VPC Peering
Go to: VPC → Peering Connections → Create
Name: EC2-RDS-Peering
Requester VPC: VPC-EC2
Accepter VPC: VPC-RDS

13. Accept Peering
Select peering → Actions → Accept
Status: Active

14. Update Route Tables
EC2 Route Table
Go to EC2-RT
Add route:
Destination	- 10.1.0.0/16	
Target -     Peering (pcx-xxxx)

 RDS Route Table
Find main route table of VPC-RDS
Edit routes:
Add:
Destination	- 10.0.0.0/16
Target -	Peering (pcx-xxxx)


15. Test Connection
SSH into EC2:
ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@<Public-IP>

16. sudo apt install mysql-client -y
17. mysql -h mydb.c32yqq8gsacb.ap-south-1.rds.amazonaws.com -u admin -p


